Key Match Events: Liam Livingstone's 87 guided England to a three-wicket win over Australia in the second T20 international
A blistering 90-run partnership off 47 balls between Livingstone and Jacob Bethell swung the game England's way
Post-Match Reflections: Stand-in captain Phil Salt expressed pride in the team's resilience after a close win
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was a winner-takes-all clash for the series in Manchester on Sunday
Australia had posted a big total of 193 for six thanks to Jake Fraser-McGurk's first international 50
